deck: Eric J Cockrell is a Chicago based illustrator of anything from books and comic books to album covers to logos and letterheads. Eric is a traditionally trained Illustrator, having graduated from The American Academy of Art in Chicago, IL with a Bachelor's Degree in Fine Arts, his major in Commercial Arts and Graphic Design. During his time at the American Academy of Art, Eric was honored by having two of pieces entered into the Academy's archives.
name: Eric J Cockrell

description: Julie Michel was born in Greeley, Colorado in 1959 and studied at the Corcoran School of Art. She made her comics coloring debut in 1986 on Fashion in Action, written and illustrated by her close friend John Snyder. Other comics credits include the three-issue Winterworld mini-series, which was illustrated by Jorge Zaffino. Michel also works as a sculptor and hopes, in the future, to work in children's book illustration.
name: Julie Michel
